[ProMED-mail thanks Dr Sher Bahadur Pun for continued contributions to ProMED-mail on scrub typhus in Nepal.

Prior to September 2015, Nepal was divided into 5 regions, which were subdivided into 14 administrative zones and then 75 districts. Sankhuwasabha, Dhankuta, Bhojpur, and Morang districts are in the Kosi Zone and Ilam district is in the Mechi Zone of the Eastern Region, referred to in the news report above. Chitwan is in the Narayani Zone of the Central Region of Nepal. Maps of Nepal can be seen at http://ncthakur.itgo.com/map04.htm (regions, zones, and districts) and http://www.healthmap.org/promed/p/139. Nepal is currently divided into 7 federal provinces, which are formed by grouping together the existing districts (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nepalese_Federal_States).

For discussions of scrub typhus, see moderator comments in prior ProMED-mail posts below. - Mod.ML]
